From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: keptuve <keptuve@keptuve.k>
Date: Tue, 9 Dec 2025 14:44:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] import and export bookmarks feature

Adds "Impport bookmarks" and "Export bookmarks" menu items to the bookmarks page.

We extend an existing `BookmarkBridge` class to talk to c++ implementation, which runs
as a `chrome::mojo::ProfileImport` service, which is not enabled in Chromium for Android.
This patch modifies the .gn files to enable just the import/export bookmarks part of it.

chrome/browser/BUILD.gn
Add bookmark_html_writer, which writes bookmarks to the browser profile (import).
Add a dependency on //chrome/browser/importer:vanadium_impl

chrome/browser/bookmarks/android/BUILD.gn
Add bookmark_import_export_helper.cc, the Vanadium specific impl.

chrome/browser/importer/BUILD.gn
Defines vanadium_impl: browser process client-side for `chrome::mojo::ProfileImport` service

chrome/common/importer/BUILD.gn
Exclude various platform specific importers.

chrome/utility/BUILD.gn
The ProfileImport service run as a utility process. Take bookmarks_file_importer.cc, exclude other.

Approx one-way execution flow:

Android Java: handle menu events -> (C++)  BookmarkBridge -> (Vanadium)  BookmarksImportExportHelper ->
(browser service launcher) RunProfileImporter ->
(trimmed down native chromium service in a separate helper process) `chrome::mojo::ProfileImport`

Originally authored by: keptuve <keptuve@keptuve.k>, ported to M146 by
quh4gko8, with initial minimization of gn files modification.
